title: What is A Heart Attack? Symptoms, Causes,Treatments And More
description: Heart disease is the number one cause of death in the U.S., and the CDC estimates that someone in the U.S. has a heart attack every 40 seconds. A heart attack happens when blood flow cannot reach the heart. Common symptoms include chest tightness, difficulty breathing, sweating, and nausea. Learn the causes, how to recognize the signs, and common treatments for heart attacks.

title: What Is Multiple Sclerosis?: Causes, MS Symptoms, & Medications
description: Multiple sclerosis (MS) is a chronic disease of the central nervous system that can cause vision problems, fatigue, weakness, and difficulty walking. This autoimmune condition can’t yet be cured, but treatments can help reduce the number of flare-ups. Find out more at GoodRx.

title: What Is Lupus? Symptoms, Causes, Treatment and More
description: From recognizing the symptoms and getting a diagnosis to preventing flares and knowing what to expect, systemic lupus erythematosus (lupus) presents challenges at every turn. Symptoms can include fatigue, joint pain, rash, and fever. Treatments usually involve medication such as anti-inflammatories and steroids. Understand the basics with this guide from GoodRx.

title: What is Ulcerative Colitis? Symptoms, Medications, & More
description: Ulcerative Colitis is an inflammatory bowel disease that targets your large intestines and colon. Symptoms often come gradually and commonly include ulcers and inflammation in your digestive tract. This condition isn’t currently curable, but there is medication to alleviate flare-ups and other associated symptoms.

title: What is Osteoporosis? Causes, Symptoms, Medications, & More
description: Osteoporosis is a bone condition that’s primarily caused by bone loss. This bone disease most often affects women because the estrogen changes that occur during menopause sharply decrease bone density. This drop in bone density affects strength and balance, which can result in serious injuries to the hips, spine, and wrists after a fall.

title: What Are Eating Disorders? Causes, Symptoms, and Treatments
description: Eating disorders like anorexia, bulimia, binge eating disorder, and orthorexia often start in teenagers but can develop at any age. An eating disorder can be difficult to overcome but counseling therapies and medication can help.  Find out the facts in this guide from GoodRx.

title: What Is Psoriasis? Symptoms, Causes, Treatments and More
description: Psoriasis is a complex, chronic autoimmune disease affecting the skin. A common symptom is dry, itchy, and scaly skin, but it can also affect your nails and joints. Psoriasis is an autoimmune disorder. Topical ointments and other medications can help alleviate symptoms, but currently there isn’t a permanent treatment.

title: What Is Polycystic Ovary Syndrome? Causes, Symptoms, Treatment And More
description: Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) is one of the most common hormone imbalances affecting women. It is usually caused by high levels of androgens and insulin. Common symptoms can include irregular periods, fertility difficulties,  acne, and obesity. Learn more about PCOS and how to treat it in this guide from GoodRx.

title: What Is Celiac Disease? Symptoms, Causes, Medications, and More
description: Celiac disease is an autoimmune disorder caused by a reaction to gluten that can lead to serious complications if left untreated. Common symptoms can include diarrhea, bloating, gas, and fatigue. The best treatment for symptoms of celiac disease is to consume a gluten-free diet. Find out the facts at GoodRx.

title: What Is Hypothyroidism? Symptoms, Causes, and Treatments
description: In hypothyroidism, the thyroid gland does not produce enough hormones for your body to perform optimally. Common symptoms include constipation, fatigue, and unexplained weight gain. Family history of autoimmune disorders raises the risk for hypothyroidism.

title: What Is Alopecia? Causes, Symptoms, Medications, and More
description: Alopecia areata is an autoimmune condition in which your immune system attacks hair follicles, causing significant hair loss. The hair loss usually begins as a circular bald patch that can occur when an individual is under severe stress. There are multiple types of alopecia that can affect any part of the body with hair. Find out how to treat alopecia in this guide from GoodRx.

title: What Is Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD): Symptoms, Stages & More
description: Chronic kidney disease, or CKD, is the gradual loss of kidney function over time. Symptoms don’t usually appear until the later stage of this irreversible condition. Learn more about CKD, including causes and treatment, with GoodRx.

title: What Is Rheumatoid Arthritis? Symptoms, Causes, Treatment, And More
description: Rheumatoid arthritis is a chronic inflammatory disease that can affect one or more joints. Common symptoms are swollen joints, joint stiffness, and fatigue. This is an autoimmune disorder in which smaller joints are typically affected first, but larger joints can be affected too, as can the skin, lungs, heart, and eyes. Read more to find out how to treat and diagnose RA, and how to live with the condition.

title: What Are Allergies? Symptoms, Causes, & Allergy Medications
description: An allergy is an uncomfortable immune response to a foreign substance. The reaction can include rashes, sneezing, swelling, and itching. Some of the most common allergies include pollen, medications, shellfish, pet dander, gluten, and dust mites.

title: What is Type 1 Diabetes? Symptoms, Causes, Medication & More
description: Type 1 diabetes is an autoimmune disease that causes a lifelong insulin shortage. Checking blood sugars, counting carbs, and taking insulin are a pain, but they can help prevent life-threatening complications. Type 1 diabetes is less common than are other types of diabetes.

title: Weight Loss: A Guide to Losing Weight in a Healthy Manner
description: Being overweight affects both your physical health and your mental health. There are many natural ways to approach weight loss, such as dieting and exercising, but keep in mind that non-scientific backed methods should be cautiously considered. Learn more about how weight affects health and how to lose weight responsibly in this guide from GoodRx.

title: What is High Blood Pressure (Hypertension)? Symptoms, Treatment And More
description: Hypertension, also known as high blood pressure, is a condition where the force of the blood against the blood vessel walls is too high. It can lead to heart complications such as heart disease and strokes. Read more to find out about diagnosis, treatment options, drug comparisons and more.

title: What Is the Flu? Symptoms, Treatment, Causes, Vaccines, & More
description: The flu, or influenza, is a common illness with symptoms including fever, sore throat, cough, and fatigue. Usually a few treatment methods such as sleep, hydration and OTC medication will treat the common flu but if your symptoms aren’t getting better within one week, reach out and see medical help. Read on to learn more about the causes of the flu, symptoms, treatments, vaccines, flu shots, and more.

title: What Is Anaphylaxis? Symptoms, Causes, Treatment And More
description: Anaphylaxis is a severe allergic reaction that can be life-threatening. Common symptoms include difficulty breathing, itching, hives, throat swelling, and even diarrhea or nausea. Anaphylaxis is most common in people with allergies to peanuts, tree nuts, bee stings, and some medications, but it can happen in anyone. If you see someone having anaphylaxis, give epinephrine as soon as possible and call 911 or get them to the nearest emergency room.

title: What Is High Cholesterol? Symptoms, Causes, Treatments And More
description: Too much cholesterol in the blood can cause fatty deposits inside blood vessels and increase the risk of heart attacks and strokes. There are two main types of cholesterol, LDL or “bad” cholesterol and HDL or “good” cholesterol. There are also triglycerides, a type of fat. Screening for abnormal cholesterol levels can help you keep on top of your risk of heart health problems.

title: What Is Asthma? Symptoms, Causes, & Treatments
description: Asthma is a condition that affects millions of Americans every year, and can be a chronic lung condition. Asthma can range from minor side effects to life-threatening situations. Common treatments for asthma include inhalers and oral steroids. Read more about asthma diagnosis, treatment options, drug comparisons, pricing information, and more.

title: What Is Generalized Anxiety Disorder? Symptoms, Causes, & More
description: Generalized anxiety disorder (GAD) is a mental health condition that causes intense and persistent worrying about situations in your daily life, along with other symptoms. GAD is one of the most common mental illnesses in the U.S. Learn about the symptoms, treatments, and more.

title: What is COPD? Causes, Symptoms, Medications, & More
description: COPD, or chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, is a type of irreversible lung disease that causes airflow blockage in and out of the lungs. Emphysema and chronic bronchitis fall into this group. GoodRx defines COPD in this article and analyzes causes, symptoms, treatments, and more.

title: What Is Endometriosis? Causes, Symptoms, Treatment And More
description: Endometriosis is an often painful condition that can cause heavy periods, abdominal pain, and difficulty becoming pregnant. Treatment options include hormone therapy and surgery. Learn more about endometriosis and treatment options in this guide from GoodRx.

title: Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)
description: Post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) can occur after a traumatic event when symptoms related to your trauma keep getting in the way of your life. Learn more about PTSD and its causes, symptoms, treatments, and medications.

title: What Is Breast Cancer? A Guide to Diagnosis, Stages, and Treatment
description: Breast cancer is the second most common type of cancer in women. Learn more about breast cancer and how it’s diagnosed. We’ll also cover causes, risk factors, treatment options, and prevention.

title: What Is Menopause? Causes, Symptoms, Treatment, And More
description: Menopause is the decline in levels of reproductive hormones that naturally occurs in people with typically female anatomy in their 40s or 50s. Common symptoms include hot flashes, brain fog, and vaginal dryness. Read on to learn what to expect during menopause and how to approach physical and emotional changes. We’ll also answer some of the most common questions about hormones, sex, and staying healthy during and after menopause.

title: What Do Substance Use Disorder and Addiction Mean?
description: How can you tell if someone is misusing substances and when it’s more than recreational. A substance use disorder is a type of mental health condition that affects millions of people worldwide. We define and look at the common symptoms, causes, and treatments of substance use disorder and addiction.

title: What Is Postpartum Depression? Defining Perinatal Depression
description: Postpartum depression/perinatal depression is a common mental health issue that many people experience. However, every person experiences it differently. Learn more about postpartum depression and how it can be treated, with GoodRx.

title: What Is Heart Failure? Symptoms, Causes, Medications and More
description: Heart failure, or the heart’s inability to pump enough blood, can be life-threatening if not managed properly. Common symptoms include shortness of breath, fatigue, and leg swelling. Find out what you need to know about heart failure at GoodRx.

title: What Is Vitiligo? Symptoms, Causes, Treatment And More
description: Vitiligo is a skin condition that can result in discolored patches on various areas of the body. Treatment can reduce the discoloration of patches on the skin but currently, does not cure it or stop it from coming back. Prescription medications and creams are needed to control symptoms.

title: What Is Crohn’s Disease? Causes, Symptoms, Medications, & More
description: Crohn’s disease is a chronic disease caused by inflammation in the digestive tract. Symptoms can range from mild to severe, but they usually develop gradually. If you see persistent changes in your bowel movements, consider a visit to your provider.  While there is no cure for Crohn’s, treatment options are available. Find out more at GoodRx.

title: What Is Presbyopia? Does It Affect Everyone as They Age?
description: Presbyopia is a vision issue typically associated with age. As we get older, our eyes have a harder time focusing up close. Presbyopia is a natural process, and it happens to everyone. Learn more about why presbyopia happens, what to expect, and what you can do about it with GoodRx.

title: What Is Abdominal Aortic Aneurysm, and How Do You Treat It?
description: An abdominal aortic aneurysm (AAA) is a potentially life-threatening condition if it’s not detected early. Explore what may cause or trigger AAA, what signs to look out for, how to screen for this heart condition, and what treatment options are available.

title: What Is Prediabetes? Symptoms, Causes,Treatments And More
description: Prediabetes is a health condition in which your blood sugar is abnormally high but not high enough to qualify as type 2 diabetes. Typically there are no symptoms, so a diagnosis is made through screening for high-risk individuals. Prediabetes is reversible with lifestyle changes such as diet, nutrition, and exercise.

title: What Is Type 2 Diabetes? Causes, Symptoms, Medications, and More
description: Type 2 diabetes is a common and serious medical condition where blood sugar levels are too high. It’s more common in older adults as opposed to children. Learn everything you need to know about diabetes symptoms, treatments, and medications.

title: What Is Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder (OCD)?
description: Obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD) is a mental illness characterized by intrusive thoughts and compulsive behaviors in response to the obsessive thoughts. From causes to symptoms and treatments, GoodRx’s guide to OCD covers all you need to know.

title: What Is Acne? Symptoms, Causes, Treatments, & More
description: Acne is a skin condition in which the hair follicles are clogged with oil and dead cells. It comes in various forms such as whiteheads and blackheads that could look unsightly. Treatments range from prescription creams to mild face wash.

title: What Are Migraines? Triggers, Auras, Medications, & More
description: A migraine is a type of headache that can cause moderate to severe pain. But it’s not just a headache. Read on to learn everything you need to know about migraines, symptoms, and treatments.

title: What is a UTI? Causes, Symptoms, Medications, and More
description: A urinary tract infection is an infection that affects any part of the urinary system which includes the kidney, bladder and urethra. Common symptoms are a strong urge to urinate, pain while urinating, and blood in urine. UTIs are more common in women than men. UTIs can go away by themselves, but it’s best to get treatment if you’re pregnant, older, or have other medical problems. If you have a fever, back pain, or vomiting, that’s another sign you need antibiotics.

title: What Is the Flu Vaccine? Flu Shot Efficacy, Ingredients, & Effects
description: Every year, flu vaccines are developed to protect against the influenza viruses that are most likely to appear during the flu seasons of fall and winter. Our flu vaccine guide tackles commonly asked questions about how the flu shot works, its ingredients, and vaccine options.

title: What is Erectile Dysfunction? Causes, Signs, & ED Medications
description: Erectile dysfunction (ED) is a man’s inability to “get hard”, or maintain a firm enough erection for satisfactory sex. Often caused by a physical or psychological condition, this sexual dysfunction isn’t necessarily a serious concern, but can cause anxiety and stress, place strain on relationships, and affect self-esteem. Learn more about ED’s causes, symptoms, and treatments, as well as the best medications and more.

title: What Is Birth Control? Options, Effectiveness, Costs, and More
description: Birth control is mainly used to prevent pregnancy. When it comes to birth control, there are plenty of options, from the pill to non-prescription methods like the ring, the patch, and IUDs, plus surgical methods and lifestyle choices as well. Learn more about your birth control options from GoodRx.

title: What Is Heart Health? Preventing Angina, Heart Attacks, Heart Failure And More
description: Taking care of your heart is something you can do every day: eating a healthy diet, doing aerobic exercise, keeping a regular sleep schedule, quitting smoking, and even lowering your stress levels. Living a heart-healthy lifestyle helps prevent heart disease from high blood pressure to heart attacks. Symptoms of heart disease include chest tightness, shortness of breath, a racing heartbeat, and even fatigue.

title: Ankylosing Spondylitis Definition, Symptoms, & Causes
description: Ankylosing spondylitis is an inflammatory arthrities that primarily impacts men. The disease affects the spine and bones where small bones in the vertebrae to fuse which decreases flexability in the spine. Learn more about the symptoms, treatments and causes of ankylosing spondylitis.

title: Coronavirus vs. the Flu: Differences, Symptoms, Treatments, & Death Rates
description: What are the differences and similarities between the flu and COVID-19? Both diseases are contagious and impact our respiratory systems, resulting in many of the same symptoms. However, the flu and COVID-19 are caused by different viruses and have different treatments, death rates, long-term symptoms, and more. Our coronavirus vs. flu guide details everything you need to know.
